description:
&lt;p&gt;Do you want to be part of a brand new crisis service with an exciting vision?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our vision is to ensure that all service users, carers and professionals have access to a service 24/7 that is able to provide support, advice and assessment in a compassionate, patient and recovery focused way. We believe that crisis is self- determined by the person and people experiencing the crisis and that this requires an empathetic and non-judgemental approach, that holds those experiencing the crisis at the very centre.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to appoint enthusiastic and dynamic Nurses, Social Workers or Occupational Therapists with experience of working within a mental health settings who are passionate about crisis work and ensuring safe and effective interventions are delivered to service users, their families and other professionals. We are looking for passionate and skilful clinicians who empower others and are able to support a culture of change within crisis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You would be working as part of a dynamic MDT providing telephone triage assessments and supporting and guiding service users through crisis in our contact centre as well as co-coordinating shifts, providing clinical oversight and support to practitioners, supporting with teaching and training opportunities, leading on staff development and being a visible role model that echoes the values of the trust and the vision of the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note this job is based on a 24/7 shift pattern and may include working across the Crisis Pathway. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In your supporting statement please ensure you demonstrate where you meet the essential and desirable criteria within the Job Description and how your skills and strengths support the trusts values as set out within the Job Description.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Benefits included with this role are:-&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS pension&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;a comprehensive in house &amp; external training programmes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;career progression&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;starting annual leave of 27 days per annum increasing to 33 days pa based on length of service (plus paid bank holidays)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;staff physio service&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;gym membership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS discounts and many more.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Please find attached our Job Description and Person Specification for more detail on your Key Accountabilities, then if you feel you have what it takes to make a difference in your local communities, click APPLY!&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Interview dates are yet to be set; you will be contacted via email and invited to book a time. These emails may go to your SPAM, so please keep checking all your emails if applying.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Please visit our Facebook and Twitter page @NSFTjobs&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Tim Smith&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title Service Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address tim.smith@nsft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 01284 719700&lt;/p&gt;
